today i practised triaging a suspicious file execution alert

## scenario
- a file called invoice_update.exe was executed from downloads folder
- this file had an unknown hash reputation
- connected to an external IP
- created a file Appdata
- and temporarily disbaled windows defender

## Suspicious Indicators
- The file was executed from the Downloads folder.
- The file hash reputation was unknown.
- The file connected to an external IP address.
- A new file was created in AppData.
- Windows Defender was temporarily disabled.

## Evidence Still Needed
- Check the file hash reputation.
- Investigate the external IP address.
- Review process logs.
- Inspect the file created in AppData.
- Check whether other devices executed the same file.

## Recommended Actions
- Isolate HR-LAPTOP-07 from the network.
- Collect evidence such as file hash, process details, and network connections.
- Submit the file or hash for malware analysis.
- Re-enable Windows Defender and run a full scan.
- Check other devices for the same file.
- Block the external IP if confirmed malicious.

## Lesson Learned
When malware is suspected, containment is important. The analyst should stop possible spread while collecting evidence.
